      "message": "{note;1) Create your color roles now, if not already created.\n\n2) Change NUMBER in {set;roles_amount;NUMBER} to the number of color roles you have.\n\n3) Change the color_role_1_id (and those for 2, 3 and 4) section(s) to the ID of your color role. \n        You can add additional color roles by copy pasting the {set;4;color_role_4_id} and changing the set;4 section to set;5 (etc for howver mnay color roles you want). \n\n4) If you have added (or removed) color roles then you would need to amend the first if statement and add in 1. {role.mention;{get;1}} (changing the 1's to the number you added i.e. 5. {role.mention;{get;5}}). \n\n5) Congrats, you have your color role action all set up.ðŸŽ‰\n\nYou can remove Use `{guild.prefix}color help` to get help with this action if you do not wnat to be told how to bring up the help menu evey time you use ?color (which would be everytime you use one of the subcommands).\n}\n\n{note;Section where users input how mnay color roles they have}\n{set;roles_amount;NUMBER}\nUse `{guild.prefix}color help` to get help with color roles.\n\n{note;section where the role ID's are assigned shorter identifier number}\n{set;3;777566775709401110}\n{set;2;810841640544501780} {set;1;766045197909360651}\n\n{note;Color Role List Embed}\n{if;{args;1};==;list;{a!ae;\n\t--title=\"Color Roles\";\n    {note;General Settings}\n            --color=\"#ca9d33\";\n            --icon=\"{user.avatarURL;365262543872327681}\";\n            --name=\"Created by: {user.tag;365262543872327681}\";\n            --footer=\"Requested by: {user.tag} | {user.id}\";\n            --footer-icon=\"{user.avatarURL}\";\n            --timestamp=\"true\";\n\t\t\t--description=\"\n\t\t1. {role.mention;{get;1}} | 2. {role.mention;{get;2}} | 3. {role.mention;{get;3}}\\n}}\n\n{note;Command which creates roles}\n{if;{args;1};==;create;\n\t{a!role;create;{args;2;infinity}}\n}\n\n{note;Command which deletes roles}\n{if;{args;1};==;delete;\n    {a!role;delete;{args;2;infinity}}\n}\n\n{note;Command which sends you a random color hex}\n{if;{args;1};==;hex;\n    {a!randomcolor}\n}\n\n{note;Command which adds the roles to a user}\n{if;{args;1};==;=;\n    {if;{math;abs({args;2})};<=;{get;roles_amount};\n        {channel.send;{user.mention} has recieved {role.name;{get;{math;abs({args;2})}}}}\n        {user.addrole;{get;{math;abs({args;2})}}};\n        That is not a valid number!ðŸ˜¡\n    }\n}\n\n{note;Command which adds the roles to a user}\n\n{note;Command which removes the roles from a user}\n{if;{args;1};==;remove;\n    {if;{math;abs({args;2})};<=;{get;roles_amount};\n        {channel.send;{user.mention} no longer has the color {role.name;{get;{math;abs({args;2})}}}}\n        {user.removerole;{get;{math;abs({args;2})}}};\n        That is not a valid number!ðŸ˜¡\n    }\n}\n\n{note;Help Menu Embed}\n{if;{args;1};==;help;\n    {a!ae;\n        {note;Field 1 Settings}\n            --field1name=\"list\";\n            --field1value=\"Fetches the list of color roles curated by the server staff.\\n\n                Example: `{guild.prefix}color list`\";\n    \n        {note;Field 2 Settings}\n            --field2name=\"help\";\n            --field2value=\"Brings up this help menu ðŸ‘‹\\n\n                Example: `{guild.prefix}color help`\";\n    \n        {note;Field 3 Settings}\n            --field3name=\"hex\";\n            --field3value=\"Returns the hex of a random color. You can then make a role using that color hex.\\n\n                Example: `{guild.prefix}color hex`\";\n    \n        {note;Field 4 Settings}\n            --field4name=\"=\";\n            --field4value=\"Gives you the color role you chose.\\n\n                Example: `{guild.prefix}color = <Color role number>`\";\n\n        {note;Field 5 Settings}\n            --field5name=\"remove\";\n            --field5value=\"Lets users remove a color role.\\n\n                Example: `{guild.prefix}color remove <Color role number>`\";\n\t\t\n        {note;Field 6 Settings}\n            --field6name=\"create\";\n            --field6value=\"Lets users create a color role.\\n\n                Example: `{guild.prefix}color create <Color role name>`\\n\n                *Note: This does not allow users to set a roles color, that still needs to be done via the server role settings*\\n\n                **Only users with the `Manage Roles` permission can perform this command**\";\n        {note;Field 7 Settings}\n            --field7name=\"delete\";\n            --field7value=\"Lets users delete a color role.\\n\n                Example: `{guild.prefix}color delete <Color role name>`\\n\n                **Only users with the `Administrator` permission can perform this command**\"; \n\n        {note;General Settings}\n            --title=\"Color Roles Help\";\n            --color=\"#ca9d33\";\n            --icon=\"{user.avatarURL;365262543872327681}\";\n            --name=\"Created by: {user.tag;365262543872327681}\";\n            --footer=\"Requested by: {user.tag} | {user.id}\";\n            --footer-icon=\"{user.avatarURL}\";\n            --timestamp=\"true\";\n            --description=\"This action lets you assign yourself a colour role from a list curated by the server staff.\\n\n            You can do `{guild.prefix}color <command>` to run one of the following commands:\"\n    }\n}",
